e Silver Children (1857, 1861 [?], 1863).</unittitle><container id="aspace_b47a5956e79a4003edb2d6491f6b5002" label="Mixed Materials" type="folder">1</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_46ed4ee338e0f9dacf8b5371cbc5734c" level="item"><did><unittitle>Treasurer's book of Local Assembly No. 406; 4 pp. only filled. (This organization was the local of the glass bottle workers' union, National Trade Assembly #143 of the Knights of Labor. Pertinent corres. and Xeroxes from selected pp. of <title>Proceedings</title> on file in this folder.)</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" certainty="approximate" era="ce" normal="1890-02/1890-12" type="inclusive">Feb.-Dec. 1890</unitdate><container id="aspace_72b7aac559dc25ae1a072a9ec435f97b" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235834]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_72f522c9df3f5d214f0561ab4e535f49" parent="aspace_72b7aac559dc25ae1a072a9ec435f97b" type="volume">13</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_7087c471218345a79e54f5c970548c0b" level="item"><did><unittitle>Payment vouchers (61 items, Nos. 25-85) authorizing Silver, as treasurer of the organization, to pay stated sum to a certain person, in most cases, George P. Pierce.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1890-02-18/1891-07-07" type="inclusive">Feb. 18, 1890-July 7, 1891</unitdate><container id="aspace_cfe850d781410cb43208600d86bbd219" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235834]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_999d516bebc13093c028efd92a5aae35" parent="aspace_cfe850d781410cb43208600d86bbd219" type="folder">2</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_65c85852402f281e7a1e5316fb994282" level="item"><did><unittitle>4 loose sheets of calculations and notes concerning dues and assessments.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce">n.d.</unitdate><container id="aspace_f1058d723c052067b3d204cfe88fafc9" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235834]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_cf58b178f13549f9af4a17557a6b9b19" parent="as